# Phase 1 In-Memory CLI Todo App Execution Steps

## Setup Tasks
1. Initialize Python environment
2. Create project directory structure with /src folder
3. Install required dependencies

## Implementation Tasks

### Task 1: Refactor todo_manager.py for In-Memory Storage
- Remove JSON persistence functionality
- Implement in-memory storage using Python list/dictionary
- Initialize empty storage on startup (volatile)
- Implement add_todo(task, description) function
- Implement list_todos() function
- Implement complete_todo(todo_id) function
- Implement delete_todo(todo_id) function
- Implement update_todo(todo_id, new_task, new_description) function
- Implement get_next_id() function
- Add proper error handling and validation

### Task 2: Enhance main.py with Update Command
- Implement argument parsing using argparse (with update command)
- Implement CLI command handlers (add, list, complete, delete, update)
- Connect CLI to todo_manager functions
- Add proper error handling
- Format output for readability

### Task 3: Test functionality
- Test add command
- Test list command
- Test complete command
- Test delete command
- Test update command
- Verify in-memory storage (no file persistence)

## Deployment Tasks
1. Verify all functionality works as expected
2. Confirm data is stored in-memory only (no persistent files)
3. Test error conditions and edge cases
4. Document usage instructions for In-Memory CLI app